        "packages/scieasy-blocks-imaging/src/scieasy_blocks_imaging/io/load_image.py"
      ],
      "reason": "Scope expansion required to satisfy SC-003 deliverable: the C1 dispatch prompt assumed LoadImage._load_tiff already parsed OME-XML from the TIFF ImageDescription tag and exposed it on Image.Meta.ome, but the committed code constructs Image.Meta(source_file=path) with no ome= field. Without read-side parsing the SC-003 round-trip test cannot demonstrate end-to-end OME preservation through SaveImage(.ome.tif) -> LoadImage. Added _ome_from_tiff helper and threaded the parsed OME through _load_tiff's two return paths (persisted + in-memory). The capability already advertises format_metadata_reads=(ome,) per FR-004, so this brings the implementation up to the advertised fidelity."
    },
